TimerHandle_t xBlinkTimer;

void vBlinkCallback(TimerHandle_t xTimer) {
    HAL_GPIO_TogglePin(LED_GPIO_Port, LED_Pin);
}

// In main, after scheduler init:
xBlinkTimer = xTimerCreate("Blink", pdMS_TO_TICKS(500), pdTRUE, NULL, vBlinkCallback);
xTimerStart(xBlinkTimer, 0);
```
Software timers run in the timer daemon task context. Don't block in the callback. For variable timing, use xTimerChangePeriod(). For one-shot: set auto-reload to pdFALSE.

